22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20cofounders%20of%20Cylake%2C%20from%20left%20to%20right%3A%20Ehud%20(Udi)%20Shamir%5CnNir%20Zuk%2C%20and%20Wilson%20Xu.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a7587b1fb3fcb42648dc66%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20cofounders%20of%20Cylake%2C%20from%20left%20to%20right%3A%20Ehud%20(Udi)%20Shamir%5CnNir%20Zuk%2C%20and%20Wilson%20Xu.%3Cp%3ECylake%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENir%20Zuk%20founded%20Palo%20Alto%20Networks%20in%202005%2C%20which%20now%20has%20a%20market%20cap%20of%20%24125%20billion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20retired%20last%20year%20and%20told%20Business%20Insider%20exclusively%20about%20his%20new%20startup%2C%20Cylake.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20will%20protect%20highly%20regulated%20companies%20and%20organizations%20that%20cannot%20upload%20their%20data%20to%20the%20cloud.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20more%20than%2025%20years%20building%20Palo%20Alto%20Networks%20into%20a%20%24125%20billion%20security%20giant%2C%20billionaire%20Nir%20Zuk%20is%20making%20a%20contrarian%20bet%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20new%20startup%2C%20Cylake%2C%20is%20rejecting%20the%20cloud-based%20model%20he%20once%20championed%2C%20instead%20building%20an%20AI-powered%2C%20hardware-based%20security%20system%20for%20governments%2C%20defense%20contractors%2C%20and%20other%20highly%20regulated%20customers%20that%20can't%20move%20sensitive%20data%20off-premises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBacked%20by%20%2445%20million%20from%20Greylock%2C%20the%20same%20firm%20that%20funded%20Palo%20Alto%20in%20its%20early%20days%2C%20Zuk%20is%20betting%20that%20a%20third%20of%20the%20market%20has%20been%20left%20behind%20in%20the%20rush%20to%20the%20cloud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20industry%20has%20overrotated%20toward%20delivering%20everything%20in%20the%20cloud%2C%20and%20that%20has%20left%20many%20of%20the%20most%20important%20customers%20stuck%2020%20years%20behind%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuk%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20exclusive%20interview%20unveiling%20the%20new%20startup%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20been%20here%20before.%20When%20he%20started%20Palo%20Alto%20Networks%20in%202005%2C%20he%20recalled%2C%20people%20told%20Zuk%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20crazy%2C%20nobody's%20going%20to%20use%20the%20cloud%20to%20consume%20cybersecurity%20services.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20he%20said%2C%20he's%20hearing%20a%20familiar%20refrain%3A%20%26quot%3BYou're%20crazy.%20Nobody%20starts%20a%20hardware%20company%20to%20run%20on%20premises%20in%202026%20in%20any%20space%2C%20not%20just%20in%20cyber%20security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalo%20Alto%20Networks%20is%20now%20the%20biggest%20standalone%20cybersecurity%20company%20in%20the%20world.%20Zuk's%20stake%20is%20estimated%20at%20%241.4%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20Forbes.%20After%20serving%20as%20chief%20technology%20officer%20for%20more%20than%20two%20decades%2C%20he%20announced%20his%20retirement%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20he%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20contrarian%20for%20starting%20a%20cloud-based%20cybersecurity%20company%20in%202005%2C%20he%20relishes%20going%20against%20the%20grain%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20like%20to%20be%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20there's%20a%20market%20out%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20threats%20skyrocket%20because%20of%20the%20growth%20of%20bad%20actors%20using%20AI%2C%20cybersecurity%20startups%20are%20booming.%20They%20raised%20nearly%20%2414%20billion%20in%202025%2C%20according%20to%20Pinpoint%20Search%20Group.%20That%20represented%20a%2047%25%20increase%20from%202024%20and%20the%20most%20funding%20since%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcybersecurity-experts-speak-possible-threats-221339546.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExperts%20have%20warned%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20war%20in%20Iran%20will%20lead%20to%20more%20attacks%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2264cac75b-7724-4630-9a27-8340699e0632%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20same%20VC%2C%2026%20years%20later%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20unusual%20for%20Silicon%20Valley%20VC%20firms%20to%20back%20a%20founder%20on%20their%20second%20or%20third%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20one's%20had%20a%20success%20as%20large%20as%20Palo%20Alto%2C%20that's%20a%20high%20bar%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Asheem%20Chandna%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Greylock%20who%20has%20known%20Zuk%20for%2030%20years%20and%20served%20on%20Palo%20Alto%20Networks'%20board%20for%2017%20years.%20%26quot%3BThe%20bar%20is%20not%20a%20small%20or%20medium%20outcome.%20The%20bar%20is%2C%20can%20we%20build%20something%20even%20larger%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChandna%20sees%20%26quot%3Ba%20hundred%20billion%20dollar%20plus%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20pointing%20to%20what%20he%20estimates%20as%20a%20third%20of%20customers%20like%20defense%2C%20regulated%20industries%2C%20and%20sovereign%20nations%20that%20can%20never%20use%20the%20cloud%20for%20sensitive%20data.%20He%20calls%20Zuk%20%26quot%3Ba%20magnet%20for%20talent%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Ba%20brilliant%20technologist%20who's%20very%20competitive%20and%20very%20customer-centric.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoining%20Zuk%20as%20cofounders%20at%20Cylake%20are%20Wilson%20Xu%2C%20who%20led%20the%20engineering%20team%20at%20Palo%20Alto%20Networks%2C%20and%20Udi%20Shamir%2C%20who%20co-founded%20SentinelOne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuk%20said%20he%20got%20the%20idea%20for%20starting%20Cylake%20years%20ago%20and%20finally%20decided%20to%20strike%20out%20on%20his%20own%20again%20when%20he%20reached%20a%20point%20last%20summer%20at%20which%20he%20felt%20his%20work%20at%20Palo%20Alto%20Networks%20was%20complete%20after%20it%20acquired%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.paloaltonetworks.com%2Fcompany%2Fpress%2F2026%2Fpalo-alto-networks-completes-acquisition-of-cyberark-to-secure-the-ai-era%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECyberArk%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ean%20identity%20security%20platform%2C%20for%20%2425%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20heard%20from%20customers%20over%20the%20years%20that%20they%20wish%20they%20could%20use%20the%20products%20that%20we%20were%20pitching%20to%20them%2C%20but%20they%20couldn't%20because%20they%20were%20in%20the%20cloud%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20something%20that%20a%20company%20that's%20built%20around%20delivering%20everything%20that%20it%20has%20from%20the%20cloud%20can%20solve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2054%2C%20already%20a%20billionaire%2C%20he%20says%20starting%20a%20new%20company%20is%20not%20about%20the%20money.%20%26quot%3BFirst%2C%20I%20like%20to%20build%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuk%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20second%2C%20if%20I%20didn't%20do%20it%2C%20nobody%20would%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounder-of-palo-alto-networks-started-a-new-cybersecurity-startup-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772719202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a758e0d3e2f1aef369eea8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounder-of-palo-alto-networks-started-a-new-cybersecurity-startup-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Just%20as%20he%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20contrarian%20for%20starting%20a%20cloud-based%20cybersecurity%20company%20in%202005%2C%20Nir%20Zuk%20relishes%20going%20the%20opposite%20way%20in%202026.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bbergman%40insider.com%20(Ben%20Bergman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounder-of-palo-alto-networks-started-a-new-cybersecurity-startup-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20a%20former%20Khosla%20partner%20who%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20investors%20in%20Groq%20is%20striking%20out%20on%20her%20own%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223164%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sandhya%20Venkatachalam%20is%20the%20managing%20partner%20of%20Axiom%20Partners.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a31f8ed3e2f1aef369be48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223506%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESandhya%20Venkatachalam%20is%20the%20managing%20partner%20of%20Axiom%20Partners.%3Cp%3EAxiom%20Partners%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESandhya%20Venkatachalam%20is%20a%20former%20Khosla%20Ventures%20partner%20who%20was%20an%20early%20investor%20in%20chipmaker%20Groq.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20launched%20her%20own%20firm%2C%20Axiom%20Partners%2C%20to%20write%20checks%20ranging%20from%20%24100%2C000%20to%20%242.5%20million.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20a%20tough%20time%20to%20strike%20out%20on%20one's%20own%20in%20VC%2C%20but%20she%20was%20able%20to%20raise%20a%20%2452%20million%20fund.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESandhya%20Venkatachalam%2C%20a%20former%20Khosla%20Ventures%20partner%20who%20was%20an%20early%20investor%20in%20chipmaker%20Groq%2C%20has%20launched%20her%20own%20firm%2C%20Axiom%20Partners%2C%20to%20make%20what%20she%20describes%20as%20nonconformist%20bets%20on%20AI%20startups%20in%20their%20infancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BContrarian%20and%20wrong%20is%20relatively%20useless%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BContrarian%20and%20right%2C%20that's%20the%20goal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20moment%20when%20venture%20capital%20is%20pulling%20back%20and%20emerging%20managers%20are%20struggling%20to%20raise%20money%2C%20Venkatachalam%20is%20leaning%20into%20risk%20with%20her%20debut%20%2452%20million%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20argues%20that%20too%20many%20large%20firms%20are%20chasing%20%26quot%3Bfully%20priced%26quot%3B%20AI%20infrastructure%20and%20crowded%20application%20startups%2C%20leaving%20little%20room%20for%20truly%20category-defining%20companies.%20With%20checks%20ranging%20from%20%24100%2C000%20to%20%242.5%20million%2C%20Axiom%20plans%20to%20invest%20at%20the%20earliest%20stages%2C%20backing%20founders%20with%20visions%20of%20how%20AI%20will%20reshape%20industries%2C%20even%20when%20the%20consensus%20says%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20really%20interested%20in%20investing%20in%20founders%20that%20have%20a%20different%20view%20of%20what%20tomorrow%20looks%20like%20and%20are%20using%20AI%20to%20build%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20category-defining%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVenkatachalam%20also%20sees%20froth%20in%20some%20AI%20applications%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20some%20big%20companies%20that%20emerge%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20of%20AI%20tools%20in%20HR%2C%20cybersecurity%2C%20and%20sales.%20%26quot%3BBut%20transformational%20companies%20rarely%20emerge%20from%20existing%20categories.%20We%20want%20to%20find%20the%20new%20category.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20do%20this%2C%20you%20need%20to%20go%20really%20early%2C%20you%20need%20to%20have%20high%20conviction%20and%20bet%20on%20founders%20when%20they're%20just%20starting%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224b258642-32cf-4d9d-ac55-8be5c3a3974e%5C%22%3EA%20tough%20time%20to%20strike%20out%20on%20your%20own%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20brutal%20time%20to%20strike%20out%20alone%20in%20venture%20capital.%20Institutional%20investors%20are%20trimming%20allocations%2C%20emerging%20managers%20are%20struggling%20to%20close%20funds%2C%20and%20solo%20GPs%20are%20under%20more%20scrutiny%20than%20they%20have%20been%20in%20years.%20Venkatachalam%20is%20also%20a%20rare%20woman%20of%20color%20in%20an%20industry%20dominated%20by%20white%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20timing%20was%20impeccable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20joked.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20jumped%20in%20and%20learned%20the%20hard%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20obstacles%2C%20Venkatachalam%20says%20she%20slightly%20exceeded%20her%20fundraising%20target%2C%20raising%20%2452%20million%20from%20limited%20partners%2C%20including%20several%20large%20multi-stage%20venture%20firms%20and%20multi-billion-dollar%20family%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20were%20drawn%20by%20access%20to%20deal%20flow%2C%20while%20others%20sought%20insight%20into%20how%20AI%20would%20reshape%20the%20businesses%20where%20they%20had%20made%20their%20fortunes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20folks%20are%20Guinea%20pigs%20for%20this%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20can%20help%20us%20diligence%20that%2C%20but%20also%20be%20potential%20customers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2206a82103-06c1-4f75-9262-01c4e77edc4b%5C%22%3EAdapting%20the%20Khosla%20playbook%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20influence%20on%20Venkatachalam's%20approach%20is%20Vinod%20Khosla%2C%20the%20billionaire%20founder%20of%20Khosla%20Ventures%2C%20who%20wrote%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20checks%20into%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20like%20Vinod%20have%20the%20broadest%20view%20of%20what%20makes%20a%20great%20founder%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20More%20than%20pattern%20matching%20on%20resumes%20or%20pedigree%2C%20he%20looked%20for%20underlying%20qualities%20and%20long-term%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20embraced%20non-consensus%20investing.%20When%20Khosla%20Ventures%20invested%20in%20OpenAI%20in%202019%2C%20she%20says%20it%20was%20still%20seen%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20nonprofit%20science%20project%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20decision%20was%20not%20unanimous%20even%20within%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20culture%20encouraged%20conviction.%20If%20an%20investor%20could%20defend%20the%20thesis%20rigorously%2C%20they%20were%20empowered%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20look%20for%20consensus%2C%26quot%3B%20Venkatachalam%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20really%20can%20back%20up%20your%20argument%20and%20you%20have%20conviction%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20explained%2C%20that%20is%20what%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVenkatachalam%20has%20brought%20on%20two%20other%20partners%2C%20including%20Evan%20Morikawa%2C%20OpenAI's%20former%20head%20of%20applied%20engineering%2C%20and%20Kipp%20Bodnar%2C%20chief%20marketing%20officer%20at%20HubSpot.%20Serial%20founder%20Paolo%20Perazzo%20is%20serving%20as%20the%20firm's%20%26quot%3Bhead%20of%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20this%20amazing%20team%20of%20operating%20partners%20who%20know%20far%20more%20about%20AI%20than%20I%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20whole%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20a%20solo%20GP%2C%20Venkatachalam%20retains%20ultimate%20decision-making%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20move%20in%20a%20very%20agile%20fashion%2C%20which%20I%20think%20is%20one%20of%20our%20greatest%20competitive%20advantages%20because%20lots%20of%20things%20are%20moving%20really%20fast%20in%20venture%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-khosla-partner-is-striking-out-on-her-own-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772719201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a31fad1fb3fcb42648abf2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-khosla-partner-is-striking-out-on-her-own-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sandhya%20Venkatachalam%2C%20a%20former%20Khosla%20Ventures%20partner%20who%20was%20an%20early%20investor%20in%20chipmaker%20Groq%2C%20has%20launched%20her%20own%20firm%2C%20Axiom%20Partners.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bbergman%40insider.com%20(Ben%20Bergman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-khosla-partner-is-striking-out-on-her-own-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUr