y%22%3A%22False%20signals%20mimicking%20GPS%20and%20GNSS%20have%20been%20creating%20trouble%20for%20flight%20operations%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20amid%20the%20ongoing%20military%20conflict.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Firan-israel-war-signal-interference-hits-passenger-planes-amid-war-in-middle-east-11173091%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20was%20more%20of%20a%20free-range%20parent%20when%20my%20kids%20were%20little.%20Now%20that%20one%20is%20old%20enough%20to%20drive%2C%20I%20track%20him.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20teen%20boy%20sits%20in%20the%20driver's%20seat%20of%20the%20family%20car%20before%20taking%20his%20two%20younger%20siblings%20to%20school%20(also%20pictured%20in%20the%20car).%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a85ae0fd4fbd083f2980df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20first%20time%20my%20son%20drove%20both%20of%20his%20siblings%20to%20school%2C%20I%20was%20glad%20I%20could%20track%20them%20on%20an%20app.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kathy%20Larson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI'm%20not%20a%20helicopter%20parent%2C%20but%20I%20did%20download%20an%20app%20to%20track%20my%20son%20once%20he%20got%20his%20license.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20apps%20provide%20peace%20of%20mind%20for%20me%20as%20my%20son%20gains%20independence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20son%20and%20his%20friends%20seem%20to%20view%20location%20tracking%20apps%20as%20a%20normal%20part%20of%20modern%20parenting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20my%20son%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-drivers-license-16-teenagers-parents-carpool-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egot%20his%20license%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20downloaded%20an%20app%20to%20track%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20swear%20I'm%20not%20one%20of%20those%20overprotective%20helicopter%20moms.%20But%20my%20husband%20was%20the%20one%20who%20took%20him%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-doesnt-want-need-drivers-license-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eget%20his%20license%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20when%20he%20came%20back%20alone%2C%20I%20asked%20him%20where%20our%20son%20was%2C%20and%20he%20casually%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20go%20to%20Hunter's%20house%20and%20then%20maybe%20to%20see%20Amiyah%20or%20maybe%20to%20Target.%20He%20said%20he%20would%20be%20home%20before%20nine%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20panicked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20even%20describe%20the%20feeling%20I%20had%2C%20but%20it%20was%20deep%20down%20in%20the%20pit%20of%20my%20stomach.%20In%20the%20mama%20bear%20parts.%20The%20sudden%20realization%20of%20my%20total%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-parents-can-learn-from-their-kids-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elack%20of%20control%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20what%20might%20happen%20to%20my%20child%20out%20there%20in%20the%20world.%20Obviously%2C%20none%20of%20us%20really%20has%20total%20control%20over%20our%20kids'%20safety%2C%20even%20when%20they're%20physically%20with%20us%2C%20but%20that%20fact%20just%20became%20terrifyingly%20real%20to%20me%20in%20that%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20couldn't%20control%20what%20happened%2C%20but%20at%20least%20I%20could%20see%20where%20he%20was.%20It%20felt%20like%20some%20semblance%20of%20control%20at%20least.%20So%20I%20downloaded%20Life360%2C%20an%20app%20that%20provides%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-stays-connected-by-tracking-phones-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereal-time%20tracking%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20called%20him%20to%20ask%20him%20to%20share%20his%20location%20with%20me.%20He%20just%20laughed%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSure%2C%20mom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2224bf922d-adc3-44fc-b7fd-2a746966598b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20just%20what%20modern%20parents%20do%20now%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20read%20that%20some%20people%20consider%20tracking%20their%20kids'%20location%20an%20invasion%20of%20their%20privacy%2C%20but%20I%20honestly%20don't%20know%20a%20single%20parent%20who%20doesn't%20use%20an%20app%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrack-teens-location-safety-reasons-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrack%20their%20teenager%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20me%2C%20it's%20just%20part%20of%20modern-day%20parenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20kids%20were%20little%2C%20I%20had%20no%20problem%20with%20the%20old-school%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpassive-parent-parenting-style-foster-independence-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efree-range%20method%3C%2Fa%3E%20our%20parents%20had%20in%20the%2080s.%20I%20was%20totally%20fine%20with%20letting%20them%20roam%20our%20very%20safe%20neighborhood%20and%20telling%20them%20to%20be%20back%20when%20the%20streetlights%20came%20on.%20But%20having%20your%20kid%20driving%20their%20own%20car%2C%20halfway%20across%20the%20county%2C%20with%20who%20knows%20who%20else%20out%20there%20on%20the%20roads%20with%20them%2C%20just%20hits%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20screenshot%20of%20where%20the%20writer's%20son%20is%20while%20using%20a%20tracking%20app.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a85bd61fb3fcb42648e605%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20enjoys%20being%20able%20to%20check%20in%20on%20her%20son's%20location%2C%20though%20she%20admits%20she%20doesn't%20do%20it%20very%20much.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kathy%20Larson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20seem%20controlling%2C%20but%20like%20anything%20else%2C%20I%20think%20it%20depends%20on%20how%20you%20use%20it.%20If%20you're%20a%20controlling%20parent%2C%20you'll%20use%20it%20in%20a%20controlling%20way.%20If%20you're%20not%2C%20it%20will%20just%20be%20a%20way%20for%20you%20to%20feel%20better%20about%20their%20safety%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteenager-wants-independence-feels-like-break-up-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eallowing%20them%20independence%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20just%20another%20resource%20to%20keep%20your%20kids%20safe%2C%20like%20the%20phones%20they%20carry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20a%20teenager%2C%20I%20had%20an%20old%20hand-me-down%20car%20that%20broke%20down%20at%20least%20once%20a%20month.%20I%20had%20no%20cell%20phone.%20My%20only%20option%20was%20to%20knock%20on%20the%20closest%20door%20and%20ask%20to%20use%20their%20phone.%20A%20few%20of%20those%20times%20were%20very%20dicey.%20I'm%20thankful%20my%20kids%20have%20the%20option%20to%20call%20me%2C%20no%20matter%20where%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e522497f-e6ae-4a5c-977f-be979fe6a82b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20kids%20think%20it's%20normal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20has%20zero%20problem%20with%20me%20tracking%20him.%20He%20just%20thinks%20it's%20normal.%20The%20only%20way%20I%20even%20knew%20about%20Life360%20was%20because%20his%20friend%20group%20uses%20the%20app%20to%20track%20each%20other%2C%20just%20because.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20most%20of%20his%20friends'%20parents%20track%20them%2C%20none%20of%20them%20seems%20to%20think%20it's%20a%20big%20deal.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20parents%20joke%20around%20that%20the%20kids%20use%20it%20more%20like%20overbearing%20parents%20than%20we%20do.%20A%20mom%20might%20be%20out%20running%20errands%20and%20get%20a%20text%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20you%20doing%20at%20Chipotle%3F%20You%20said%20you%20were%20going%20to%20the%20grocery%20store.%26quot%3B%20Then%2C%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20bring%20me%20a%20burrito%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc916b75-8945-43fd-a187-6f49339c32d1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20don't%20stalk%20him%20on%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20check%20it%20all%20the%20time.%20I%20don't%20even%20look%20at%20it%20every%20day.%20The%20only%20time%20I've%20really%20stalked%20him%20was%20the%20first%20day%20of%20school%20this%20year%2C%20when%20he%20drove%20his%20two%20younger%20siblings%20to%20school%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20As%20they%20drove%20away%2C%20I%20turned%20to%20my%20husband%20and%20gasped%2C%20%26quot%3BOur%20whole%20life%20is%20in%20that%20car.%26quot%3B%20He%20flashed%20me%20his%20phone%2C%20%26quot%3BAlready%20tracking%20them.%26quot%3B%20As%20we%20finished%20our%20coffee%2C%20we%20watched%20them%20on%20Life360%20the%20entire%20way%2C%20all%2018%20minutes.%20But%20I%20haven't%20done%20that%20any%20other%20day%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20typically%20only%20check%20it%20if%20it's%20getting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-bans-curfews-malls-theme-parks-chick-fil-a-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eclose%20to%20curfew%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20he%20hasn't%20texted%20to%20say%20he's%20left%20yet.%20Or%20if%20it's%20way%20past%20the%20time%20tennis%20or%20volleyball%2C%20or%20soccer%20practice%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20over%2C%20and%20he%20isn't%20home%20yet.%20Or%20the%20time%20there%20was%20a%20shooting%20near%20our%20local%20T.J.%20Maxx%2C%20and%20he%20and%20his%20girlfriend%20were%20out%20shopping%20at%20the%20time.%20I%20don't%20really%20track%20him%20day-to-day%3B%20it's%20just%20a%20fallback.%20In%20case%20something%20happens%2C%20and%20I%20need%20to%20know%20where%20he%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20actually%20use%20it%20to%20track%20my%2077-year-old%20mom%20far%20more%20often%20than%20I%20do%20my%20kids.%20And%20yes%2C%20I%20have%20her%20permission.%20She%20asked%20me%20to%20track%20her%20when%20my%20dad%20died%2C%20so%20someone%20would%20know%20where%20she%20is%2C%20just%20in%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20yet%20sure%20if%20I'