sinsider.com%2Fwho-is-greg-abel-warren-buffett-successor-berkshire-hathaway%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGreg%20Abel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20succeeded%20Warren%20Buffett%20as%20Berkshire%20Hathaway's%20CEO%20in%20January%2C%20has%20pledged%20to%20use%20his%20entire%20paycheck%20each%20year%20to%20purchase%20Berkshire%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbel%2C%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fberkshire-hathaway-greg-abel-ceo-salary-warren-buffett-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eannual%20salary%20for%202026%20is%20%2425%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20during%20a%20CNBC%20interview%20on%20Thursday%20that%20he%20had%20just%20spent%20all%20of%20his%20after-tax%20pay%20of%20around%20%2415%20million%20on%20Berkshire's%20Class%20A%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20regulatory%20filing%20confirmed%20that%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Abel%20purchased%2021%20shares%20for%20around%20%24730%2C000%20each%2C%20for%20a%20total%20outlay%20of%20%2415.3%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerkshire's%20new%20boss%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20%26quot%3Bdemonstrate%20alignment%26quot%3B%20with%20his%20shareholders%20by%20putting%20more%20of%20his%20own%20money%20on%20the%20line.%20He%20also%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bexcited%26quot%3B%20to%20own%20more%20of%20the%20company%20as%20he%20believes%20it%20has%20a%20bright%20future%2C%20and%20would%20continue%20plowing%20his%20whole%20salary%20into%20Berkshire%20stock%20each%20year%20%26quot%3Bas%20long%20as%20I'm%20the%20CEO.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbel%20said%20the%20commitment%20was%20his%20idea%20and%20would%20amount%20to%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20my%20after-tax%20dollars%26quot%3B%20over%20time.%20He%20added%20that%20when%20he%20spoke%20to%20Buffett%20about%20it%2C%20the%20legendary%20investor%20approved%20because%20it%20was%20unique%20in%20corporate%20America%20and%20felt%20%26quot%3Bso%20Berkshire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett%20earned%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-annual-salary-compensation-40-years-2021-3-1030229588%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%24100%2C000%20salary%20for%20more%20than%2040%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20Berkshire%20CEO%2C%20and%20in%20recent%20years%20returned%20half%20that%20sum%20to%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20his%20personal%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BOracle%20of%20Omaha%2C'%26quot%3B%20who%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-warren-buffett-spends-money-net-worth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2099%25%20of%20his%20net%20worth%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Berkshire%20stock%2C%20has%20long%20expressed%20hope%20that%20his%20successor%20would%20also%20put%20a%20significant%20chunk%20of%20his%20personal%20wealth%20into%20the%20company%20to%20align%20their%20interests%20with%20Berkshire%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-q2-earnings-stocks-buybacks-abel-bhe-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esold%20his%20stake%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20Energy%20to%20Berkshire%20for%20%24870%20million%20before%20taxes%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20transaction%20sparked%20calls%20for%20him%20to%20invest%20some%20of%20the%20proceeds%20in%20Berkshire%20and%20get%20some%20more%20%26quot%3Bskin%20in%20the%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20only%20owned%20around%20%243%20million%20of%20the%20company's%20stock%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20obliged%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-greg-abel-berkshire-hathaway-energy-stock-price-succession-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Espending%20%2468%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20168%20Class%20A%20shares%20in%20September%202022%2C%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-successor-greg-abel-berkshire-hathaway-s