20in%20the%20initial%20phase%20of%20Operation%20Epic%20Fury.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUS%20officials%20have%20highlighted%20less%20obvious%20but%20important%20elements%20of%20warfare%20in%20recent%20conflicts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20assess%20that%20winning%20these%20hidden%20battles%20is%20essential%20to%20victory%20in%20modern%20war.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECyber%2C%20space%2C%20and%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%20warfare%20can%20be%20decisive.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20opening%20hours%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-us-general-rundown-opening-days-iran-attack-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOperation%20Epic%20Fury%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20US%20targeted%20Iranian%20combat%20assets%20with%20firepower%20that%20isn't%20as%20visible%20as%20a%20missile%20but%20is%20devastatingly%20effective%20in%20modern%20warfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20movers%26quot%3B%20were%20US%20space%20and%20cyber%20forces%2C%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Joint%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff%20Gen.%20Dan%20Caine%20said%20Monday.%20They%20disrupted%2C%20degraded%2C%20and%20blinded%20Iran%2C%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20massive%20follow-on%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-general-details-us-military-raid-that-captured-venezuelas-maduro-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOperation%20Absolute%20Resolve%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20Venezuela%20earlier%20in%20the%20year%20involved%20similar%20tactics.%20As%20the%20helicopters%20carrying%20special%20operations%20forces%20approached%20its%20shores%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20United%20States%20began%20layering%20different%20effects%20provided%20by%20SPACECOM%2C%20CYBERCOM%2C%20and%20other%20members%20of%20the%20interagency%20to%20create%20a%20pathway%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20top%20general%20said%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Space%20Command%20and%20Cyber%20Command%20also%20provided%20critical%20support%20to%20Operation%20Midnight%20Hammer%2C%20which%20saw%20the%20US%20hit%20Iran's%20nuclear%20facilities%20last%20summer.%20All%20three%20of%20these%20operations%20have%20been%20against%20well-armed%20nation-states%2C%20not%20terrorist%20groups%20or%20insurgencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20each%20of%20these%20operations%2C%20non-kinetic%20effects%2C%20the%20capabilities%20beyond%20physically%20shooting%20and%20destroying%20a%20target%2C%20played%20an%20important%20role.%20Non-kinetic%20cyber%2C%20space%2C%20and%20electronic%20warfare%20are%20ways%20militaries%20can%20jam%20signals%2C%20hack%20networks%2C%20or%20disrupt%20satellites%20to%20blind%20or%20confuse%20an%20enemy%20without%20blowing%20something%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%2C%20the%20full%20range%20of%20all%20types%20of%20light%20energy%2C%20from%20low-energy%20radio%20waves%20to%20high-energy%20gamma%20rays%2C%20is%20a%20particularly%20crucial%20battlespace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20summers%20ago%2C%20the%20commander%20of%20the%20US%20Air%20Force's%20350th%20Spectrum%20Warfare%20Wing%20spoke%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-electronic-warfare-battle-demanding-more-of-ukrainian-soldiers-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eelectronic%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum.%20He%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20spectrum%20is%20a%20bad%20place%20to%20be%20second%2C%20and%20if%20we%20lose%20in%20the%20spectrum%2C%20or%20are%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eunable%20to%20affect%20the%20spectrum%2C%20the%20joint%20force%20will%20lose%2C%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20lose%20very%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20with%20Iran%20reinforces%20that%20being%20able%20to%20fight%20effectively%20in%20the%20hidden%20battles%20is%20crucial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224251%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Plumes%20of%20smoke%20rise%20following%20reported%20explosions%20in%20Tehran%20on%20March%202%2C%202026%2C%20after%20Iran's%20supreme%20leader%2C%20Ayatollah%20Ali%20Khamenei%2C%20was%20killed%20on%20February%2028%2C%20in%20a%20large%20US%20and%20Israeli%20attack%2C%20prompting%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20retaliatory%20missile%20strikes%20from%20Iran.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a84757fd4fbd083f297e5a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222834%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20and%20Israel%20have%20carried%20out%20widespread%20airstrikes%20in%20Iran.%3Cp%3EMowj%2FMiddle%20East%20Images%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20look%20at%20warfare%20in%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20the%20use%2C%20the%20exploitation%2C%20the%20denial%20of%20the%20EM%20%5Belectromagnetic%5D%20spectrum%20is%20absolutely%20foundational%20to%20victory%2C%26quot%3B%20Houston%20Cantwell%2C%20a%20retired%20US%20Air%20Force%20brigadier%20general%20and%20expert%20at%20the%20Mitchell%20Institute%20for%20Aerospace%20Studies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20it%20was%20important.%20In%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20it's%20essential%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EModern%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%20warfare%20took%20shape%20during%20World%20War%20II%2C%20when%20radar%2C%20signals%20intelligence%2C%20and%20jamming%20became%20valuable%20tools.%20The%20technology%20and%20speed%20have%20evolved%20dramatically%20in%20the%2080%20years%20since%2C%20but%20the%20core%20logic%20%E2%80%94%20detect%2C%20disrupt%2C%20deceive%2C%20and%20protect%20use%20of%20the%20spectrum%20%E2%80%94%20still%20underpins%20military%20operations%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bfreedom%20of%20action%20in%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20said%20in%20its%20October%202020%20strategy%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20a%20required%20precursor%20to%20the%20successful%20conduct%20of%20operations%20in%20all%20domains.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20Israel%20have%20targeted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-israel-fight-iran-air-defenses-vital-in-modern-war-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIran's%20air%20defenses%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20clear%20the%20way%20for%20air%20operations%2C%20potentially%20blinding%20them%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-jammed-new-tech-ngc2-electronic-warfare-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejamming%20or%20disabling%20the%20radars%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20rely%20on.%20They%20may%20also%20have%20disrupted%20communications%20between%20command%20centers%2C%20radars%2C%20air%20bases%2C%20and%20fighter%20jets%20using%20jamming%2C%20cyber%2C%20and%20other%20non-kinetic%20tools.%20Specifics%20are%20unclear%2C%20but%20the%20US%20has%20many%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaintaining%20dominance%20in%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%20is%20as%20vital%20as%20denying%20the%20enemy's%20use%20of%20it%2C%20Cantwell%20said%2C%20especially%20for%20weapons%20that%20rely%20on%20laser%2C%20GPS%2C%20or%20satellite%20navigation.%20If%20the%20spectrum%20is%20denied%2C%20then%20those%20precision%20weapons%20might%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%26quot%3B%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatching%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20US%20has%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20how%20its%20precision%20weapons%2C%20like%20HIMARS-fired%20Guided%20Multiple%20Launch%20Rocket%20Systems%20and%20air-launched%20Joint%20Direct%20Attack%20Munitions%2C%20fair%20against%20electronic%20interference.%20Kyiv's%20forces%20have%20previously%20observed%20major%20drops%20in%20the%20accuracy%20of%20weapons%20because%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-cheap-electronic-warfare-keeps-beating-us-precision-weapons-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERussia's%20electronic%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20battlefield%20has%20been%20dominated%20by%20elements%20of%20electronic%20warfare%2C%20as%20both%20sides%20jam%20communications%2C%20drones%2C%20weapons%2C%20and%20other%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20holds%20an%20electronic%20warfare%20device%20in%20a%20workshop.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a883671fb3fcb42648ea83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20provided%20years%20of%20lessons%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20controlling%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum.%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20said%20the%20war%20has%20demonstrated%20the%20widespread%20effects%20these%20tactics%20can%20have%2C%20and%20over%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20US%20military%20officials%20have%20often%20discussed%20the%20importance%20of%20owning%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-showing-us-troops-fight-hide-in-electromagnetic-spectrum-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eelectromagnetic%20spectrum%20in%20future%20conflicts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20also%20acknowledging%20they%20expect%20difficulties%20in%20doing%20so%2C%20especially%20against%20a%20peer%20adversary%20like%20Russia%20or%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFighting%20within%20cyberspace%20is%20an%20important%20related%20element%20that%20is%20largely%20hidden%20in%20combat%20but%20of%20great%20importance%2C%20and%20while%20the%20exact%20uses%20of%20cyber%20warfare%20in%20recent%20US%20fights%20haven't%20been%20publicly%20disclosed%2C%20its%20potential%20impacts%20are%20notable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECyber%20warfare%20is%20a%20very%20useful%20tool%20in%20the%20disruptive%20phase%20of%20an%20operation%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20critical%20for%20%26quot%3Bsupporting%20reconnaissance%20and%20broader%20intelligence-gathering%20efforts%20in%20preparation%20for%20the%20operation%20and%20in%20planning%20its%20subsequent%20phases%2C%26quot%3B%20Louise%20Marie%20Hurel%2C%20a%20cybersecurity%20expert%20at%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20who%20has%20consulted%20for%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20approach%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnational-guard-units-help-defend-against-cyber-attacks-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecyber%20operations%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20varied%20between%20recent%20campaigns%2C%20but%20one%20thing%20is%20becoming%20clear%2C%20Hurel%20said.%20Cyber%20was%20previously%20considered%20decisive%20on%20its%20own%2C%20but%20now%20there%20is%20an%20increasing%20understanding%20that%20%26quot%3Bcyber%20is%20more%20useful%20as%20an%20enabler%20and%20force%20multiplier%20within%20broader%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnseen%20non-kinetic%20effects%2C%20from%20cyber%20to%20electronic%20warfare%2C%20that%20are%20able%20to%20confuse%20or%20weaken%20enemies%20at%20key%20moments%20in%20battle%20can%20clear%20the%20way%20for%20kinetic%20strikes%2C%20while%20protecting%20reliable%20access%20to%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%20on%20defense%20ensures%20that%20forces%20can%20communicate%20and%20operate%20and%20also%20deny%20the%20enemy%20forces%20the%20chance%20to%20interfere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20capabilities%20that%20militaries%20can't%20afford%20to%20execute%20operations%20without.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20military%20%26quot%3Bmight%20not%20win%20the%20war%20through%20spectrum%20dominance%20alone%2C%26quot%3B%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20electronic%20warfare%20and%20air%20defense%20expert%20Thomas%20Withington%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20lose%20the%20battle%20in%20the%20spectrum%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20win%20the%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-war-with-iran-shows-unseen-battle-vital-modern-war-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772707261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8a4c0d3e2f1aef36a0112%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-war-with-iran-shows-unseen-battle-vital-modern-war-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fighting%20a%20modern%20war%20depends%20heavily%20on%20hidden%20battles.%20It's%20not%20only%20about%20how%20many%20bombs%20a%20military%20can%20drop%20on%20its%20enemy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-war-with-iran-shows-unseen-battle-vital-modern-war-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20new%20hedge%20fund%20trying%20to%20deliver%20big%20returns%20without%20expensive%20PMs%20has%20lost%20money%20since%20it%20launched%20last%20summer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trader%20looking%20at%20computers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8ca39d3e2f1aef36a03fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22534%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESIMON%20DAWSON%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETaproot%20Management%2C%20run%20by%20David%20Lin%20and%20ex-Two%20Sigma%20exec%20Jason%20Beverage%2C%20has%20lost%20money%20since%20launching.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20firm%20aims%20to%20deliver%20multistrategy-like%20returns%20without%20the%20high%20costs%20that%20come%20with%20a%20large%20staff.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKevin%20Merritt%2C%20the%20firm's%20director%20of%20research%2C%20is%20also%20leaving%20the%20fund%2C%20Business%20Insider%20learned.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETaproot%20Management%20is%20hoping%20to%20bring%20a%20new%20investing%20model%20to%20the%20%245.2%20trillion%20hedge%20fund%20industry.%20So%20far%2C%20though%2C%20the%20young%20firm%20and%20its%20innovative%20structure%20haven't%20made%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manager%2C%20which%20received%20%24250%20million%20in%20backing%20from%20massive%20Canadian%20pension%20CPPIB%2C%20launched%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%20last%20year%20and%20lost%20roughly%201%25%20in%20its%20first%20six%20months%20of%20trading%2C%20two%20people%20close%20to%20Taproot%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20firm%20has%20also%20lost%20money%20through%20the%20first%20two%20months%20of%202026%2C%20though%20the%20exact%20amount%20of%20the%20drawdown%20is%20unclear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaproot%20is%20run%20by%20founder%20David%20Lin%2C%20previously%20of%20Tamridge%20and%20Glenview%20Capital%2C%20and%20by%20Jason%20Beverage%2C%20its%20chief%20investment%20officer%2C%20a%20former%20executive%20at%20quant%20giant%20Two%20Sigma.%20They%20manage%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falpha-capture-hedge-funds-quantamental-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealpha%20capture%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20recreating%20the%20steady%20returns%20of%20multistrategy%20managers%20like%20Citadel%20and%20Millennium%20without%20the%20high%20costs%20that%20come%20with%20dozens%20of%20human%20portfolio%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20computer-driven%20fund%20has%20battled%20a%20tough%20quant%20environment%20since%20launch%3B%20July%20was%20described%20as%20a%20part%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquant-hedge-funds-losses-summer-cubist-qube-man-group-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20long%2C%20slow%20bleed%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20for%20quant%20funds%2C%20and%20the%20start%20of%202026%20saw%20managers%20like%20Renaissance%20Technologies%20and%20Engineers%20Gate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frenaissance-schonfeld-engineers-gate-quants-lost-money-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elose%20money%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fund%20has%20also%20lost%20its%20onetime%20director%20of%20research%2C%20Kevin%20Merritt%2C%20who%20was%20also%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20firm.%20Merritt's%20LinkedIn%20states%20he%20began%20his%20garden%20leave%20in%20March.%20He%20joined%20the%20firm%20before%20it%20began%20trading%20last%20July%20and%20previously%20worked%20at%20Wedbush%20and%20the%20now-shuttered%20Aptigon%20stockpicking%20unit%20at%20Citadel.%20His%20responsibilities%20have%20been%20subsumed%20by%20Ted%20Orenstein%2C%20a%20former%20investor%20for%20several%20big-name%20funds%2C%20including%20SAC%2C%20Millennium%2C%20and%2C%20most%20recently%2C%20Walleye%2C%20who%20joined%20Taproot%20after%20launch%20as%20head%20of%20equities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manager%20and%20Merritt%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Taproot%2C%20experienced%20investment%20analysts%20feed%20their%20investment%20ideas%20into%20the%20firm's%20internal%20platform%2C%20where%20an%20algorithm%20ultimately%20makes%20investment%20decisions.%20Hiring%20analysts%20instead%20of%20PMs%20helps%20keep%20the%20fund's%20costs%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20similar%20in%20many%20ways%20to%20the%20central%20books%20run%20by%20large%20funds%2C%20which%20invest%20the%20best%20ideas%20from%20their%20PMs%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20the%20original%20alpha-capture%20fund%2C%20Marshall%20Wace's%20well-known%20TOPS%20strategy.%20TOPS%2C%20however%2C%20is%20created%20by%20taking%20in%20external%20investment%20ideas%20and%20research%20from%20sources%20such%20as%20sell-side%20analysts%2C%20not%20by%20internal%20investment%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultistrategy%20managers%20have%20become%20increasingly%20attractive%20to%20large%20institutional%20investors%20like%20pensions%20and%20sovereign%20wealth%20funds%20because%20of%20their%20reputation%20for%20strong%20returns%20regardless%20of%20the%20market%20environment.%20But%20the%20industry's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-hedge-fund-career-multistrategy-portfolio-manager-churn-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewar%20for%20talent%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20driven%20up%20costs%20for%20end%20investors%2C%20creating%20demand%20for%20a%20cheaper%2C%20multistrategy-like%20offering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20Haynes%2C%20Point72's%20former%20president%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorias-research-launch-strategy-fees-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20set%20out%20to%20create%3C%2Fa%3E%20something%20similar%20to%20Taproot%20in%202024%2C%20but%20Norias%20Research%2C%20the%20launch%2C%20never%20got%20off%20the%20ground.%20Meanwhile%2C%20David%20Stemerman's%20Centerbook%20Partners%20now%20runs%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcenterbook-partners-hedge-fund-using-other-firms-to-invest-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelies%20on%20a%20network%20of%20external%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20its%20investment%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaproot-management-hedge-fund-performance-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772707261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8ca5c1fb3fcb42648f213%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaproot-management-hedge-fund-performance-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Taproot%20Management%20feeds%20ideas%20from%20its%20analysts%20into%20its%20internal%20platform%20to%20make%20its%20investment%20decisions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bsaacks%40businessinsider.com%20(Bradley%20Saacks)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaproot-management-hedge-fund-performance-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Know%20all%20about%20'KGF'%20villain%20Ramachandra%20Raju%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772707223000%2C%22visual%22%3A%2